<subSubSection id="F8EE6509915C2C6889D5ABE4FB79F817" pageId="3" pageNumber="220" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B04B3682915C2C6889D5ABE4FB79F817" blockId="3.[151,1437,1742,2019]" pageId="3" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis id="8280EA90915C2C6889D5ABE4FEEEF96A" bold="true" box="[151,273,1742,1767]" pageId="3" pageNumber="220">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Small species (
<quantity id="770C9B67915C2C68888AABE4FDD3F96A" box="[456,556,1742,1767]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="220" unit="mm" value="6.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="6.0">6–7 mm</quantity>
). Scutum (
<figureCitation id="28CF2A07915C2C688BEAABE4FD0EF96A" box="[680,753,1742,1767]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1359,1381]" captionTargetBox="[349,1238,186,1322]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[340,1246,175,1337]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Dorsal view of male mesonotum, with bare spots indicated by a, b and c. A – B: Brachyopa minima sp. nov.; C – D: Brachyopa quadrimaculosa. Scale = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270668/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="220">
Figs 
<number id="063C24A5915C2C688BA1ABE5FD0EF96A" box="[739,753,1743,1767]" pageId="3" pageNumber="220" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A, B) covered with grey microtrichia except: pair of small bare spots posteromedian to the postpronotum; a pair of large bare spots anterior to transverse suture and median to notopleural sulcus; spots at the median ends of transverse sulcus covered by brown microtrichia; postalar callus with a bare spot; two stripes bare of microtrichia on posterior part of scutum located laterally. Male terminalia on 
<figureCitation id="28CF2A07915C2C6889D5AA74FF00F8FA" box="[151,255,1886,1911]" captionStart-0="FIGURE 4" captionStart-1="FIGURE 5" captionStartId-0="7.[151,250,980,1002]" captionStartId-1="8.[151,250,1222,1244]" captionTargetBox-0="[294,1293,205,950]" captionTargetBox-1="[282,1312,193,1191]" captionTargetId-0="figure@7.[286,1301,195,958]" captionTargetId-1="figure@8.[271,1316,193,1200]" captionTargetPageId-0="7" captionTargetPageId-1="8" captionText-0="FIGURE 4. Lateral view of male terminalia of Brachyopa minima sp. nov.; A – B: epandrium and hypandrium; C: aedeagus. Scale = 0.25 mm." captionText-1="FIGURE 5. Dorsal view of male terminalia of Brachyopa minima sp. nov. A: epandrium; B: surstylus (SEM); C: hypandrium; D: apex of hypandrium (SEM). Scale = 0.25 mm." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/270669/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/270670/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="220">
Figs 
<number id="063C24A5915C2C688990AA74FF00F8FA" box="[210,255,1886,1911]" pageId="3" pageNumber="220" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5</number>
</figureCitation>
; surstylus with well-developed ventral lobe (
<figureCitation id="28CF2A07915C2C688A4DAA74FCA5F8FA" box="[783,858,1886,1911]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,980,1002]" captionTargetBox="[294,1293,205,950]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[286,1301,195,958]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Lateral view of male terminalia of Brachyopa minima sp. nov.; A – B: epandrium and hypandrium; C: aedeagus. Scale = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270669/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="220">
Figs 
<number id="063C24A5915C2C688A0EAA75FCA5F8FA" box="[844,858,1887,1911]" pageId="3" pageNumber="220" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A, 
<number id="063C24A5915C2C688AC9AA74FC66F8FA" box="[907,921,1886,1911]" pageId="3" pageNumber="220" value="5.0">5</number>
A); dorsal and ventral margins of surstylus straight (
<figureCitation id="28CF2A07915C2C6889B8AAA8FEBFF817" box="[250,320,1922,1947]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,980,1002]" captionTargetBox="[294,1293,205,950]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[286,1301,195,958]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Lateral view of male terminalia of Brachyopa minima sp. nov.; A – B: epandrium and hypandrium; C: aedeagus. Scale = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270669/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="220">
Figs 
<number id="063C24A5915C2C688870AAA8FEBFF817" box="[306,320,1922,1946]" pageId="3" pageNumber="220" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A, 
<number id="063C24A5915C2C688828AAA8FE87F816" box="[362,376,1922,1947]" pageId="3" pageNumber="220" value="5.0">5</number>
A); hypandrium wide with complex apical appendages (
<figureCitation id="28CF2A07915C2C688AB0AAA8FBC6F816" box="[1010,1081,1922,1947]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1222,1244]" captionTargetBox="[282,1312,193,1191]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[271,1316,193,1200]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Dorsal view of male terminalia of Brachyopa minima sp. nov. A: epandrium; B: surstylus (SEM); C: hypandrium; D: apex of hypandrium (SEM). Scale = 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/270670/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="220">
Figs 
<number id="063C24A5915C2C688D69AAA8FBC6F816" box="[1067,1081,1922,1947]" pageId="3" pageNumber="220" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
C, D).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
